16/10/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Croatian journalist Josip Jovic pleaded not guilty to charges of contempt of court at the UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague Friday (14 October). The former editor-in-chief of Slobodna Dalmacija newspaper appeared before the tribunal one day after being released from a prison in Split, following a one-week detention. Jovic was allowed to return to Croatia after he entered his plea. He stands accused of revealing the identity of a protected witness. (Vecernji list, Novi list - 15/10/05; HIC)
